  • Method Details

    • uiReadyHOPPolicyLocation

      public static PolicyLocationBuilder uiReadyHOPPolicyLocation()
      Creates a builder that can be used to build a UI ready policy location. The location will have the following fields set:
      • Policy - if this location is built within the context of a claim or policy then it will use the existing policy. Otherwise it will create a new homeowners (HOP) policy and claim
      • LocationNumber - set to the next available location number on the policy
      • Address - set to a UI ready USA address
      The builder will also add a risk unit to the policy referring to the new policy location, assuming there is not already one present (which could happen if this builder is called while creating a risk unit)
      Returns:
      the newly created builder

    • withRiskUnitIfNonePresent

      public PolicyLocationBuilder withRiskUnitIfNonePresent()
      If there is no existing risk unit on the policy that refers to this policy location, then create a new one and auto set its risk unit number. Does nothing if there already is a risk unit on the policy that refers to this location. Must be called after onPolicy().
      Returns:
      the modified builder

    • clearWithRiskUnitIfNonePresent

      public PolicyLocationBuilder clearWithRiskUnitIfNonePresent()
      Can be used to cancel the effects of calling withRiskUnitIfNonePresent(). Rarely useful but could be used to, for example, modify the behavior of the ui ready builder
      Returns:
      the modified builder
